  "prompt": "How can I link my valid Aadhaar card to the SBI?",
  "response": "You can link your Aadhaar card to your SBI account through several methods:\n\n**1. Online (SBI Internet Banking):**\n\n*   **Prerequisites:** You must have an active SBI internet banking account.\n*   **Steps:**\n    *   Log in to your SBI internet banking account.\n    *   Navigate to \"My Accounts & Profile\".  The exact location might vary slightly depending on the internet banking interface, but look for something similar.\n    *   Look for options like \"Link Aadhaar,\" \"Update Aadhaar,\" or \"Aadhaar Seeding\".\n    *   Enter your Aadhaar number.\n    *   Submit the request.\n    *   You might receive an OTP (One-Time Password) on your registered mobile number for verification. Enter the OTP if prompted.\n    *   After successful verification, your Aadhaar will be linked to your account. You will likely see a confirmation message or status update.\n\n**2. Online (SBI YONO App):**\n\n*   **Prerequisites:** You must have the SBI YONO App installed on your smartphone and be registered.\n*   **Steps:**\n    *   Log in to the SBI YONO App.\n    *   Navigate to \"Services\" or \"Service Request\".  The menu options might be slightly different depending on the app version.\n    *   Look for the option \"Link Aadhaar\" or \"Aadhaar Seeding\".\n    *   Select your SBI account number.\n    *   Enter your Aadhaar number.\n    *   Submit the request.\n    *   You might receive an OTP (One-Time Password) on your registered mobile number for verification.  Enter the OTP if prompted.\n    *   After successful verification, your Aadhaar will be linked to your account.\n\n**3. SMS:**\n\n*   **Prerequisites:** Your mobile number must be registered with SBI for SMS banking.\n*   **Steps:**\n    *   Compose an SMS in the following format: `UID<space><Aadhaar Number><space><Account Number>`\n    *   Send the SMS to `567676`.\n    *   Example: `UID 123456789012 12345678901`\n    *   SBI will process your request and send you a confirmation SMS.  Be sure to send the SMS from your registered mobile number.\n\n**4. Visit an SBI Branch:**\n\n*   **Steps:**\n    *   Visit your nearest SBI branch.\n    *   Request an Aadhaar Seeding Form (or Linking Form) from the bank official.\n    *   Fill out the form accurately, providing your Aadhaar number and account details.\n    *   Submit the form along with a self-attested copy of your Aadhaar card.  (Self-attestation means signing the copy of your Aadhaar card with your name and date).\n    *   The bank official will verify your details and process your request.\n    *   You will likely receive an acknowledgment receipt.\n\n**5. ATM:**\n\n*   **Some ATMs may offer this facility. Check if your SBI ATM provides the option to link Aadhaar.**\n*   **Steps:**\n    *   Visit an SBI ATM.\n    *   Insert your ATM card and enter your PIN.\n    *   Look for options like \"Services\", \"Registration\", or \"Other Services\".\n    *   Find the \"Aadhaar Seeding\" or \"Aadhaar Registration\" option.\n    *   Enter your Aadhaar number.\n    *   Confirm the details.\n    *   You may receive a confirmation slip.\n\n**Important Notes & Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **Mobile Number Registration:** Ensure your mobile number is registered with your SBI account for online methods and SMS. If not, visit your branch to register or update your mobile number.\n*   **Aadhaar Details:**  Ensure that the name and other details on your Aadhaar card match the details in your SBI account. Discrepancies can lead to rejection.\n*   **Confirmation:** After linking, check your account statement or contact the bank to confirm that your Aadhaar has been successfully linked.  Some online portals might show the status after logging in.\n*   **Multiple Accounts:** If you have multiple SBI accounts, you need to link your Aadhaar to each account separately.\n*   **Security:** Never share your Aadhaar number or OTP with anyone over the phone or through unsolicited emails/SMS. SBI will never ask for this information in such a manner.\n*   **NPCI Linking:**  Linking your Aadhaar to your bank account is crucial for receiving Direct Benefit Transfers (DBT) from the government (e.g., subsidies, pensions).  While linking your Aadhaar to SBI is important, also ensure your SBI account is mapped to NPCI (National Payments Corporation of India) for DBT. The bank will usually take care of this automatically when you link your Aadhaar. You can check the status of your Aadhaar-NPCI mapping on the UIDAI website.\n*   **Checking Aadhaar Linking Status:**  You can use the UIDAI (Unique Identification Authority of India) website (uidai.gov.in) to check which bank accounts are linked to your Aadhaar number.\n\nIf you face any difficulties, it is best to visit your SBI branch for assistance.  They can guide you through the process and resolve any issues.\n",
